definitions.definition: ( transitive ) To beat, smack or slap a person's buttocks , with the bare hand or other object, as punishment, or for sexual gratification.
( transitive ) To soundly defeat , to trounce .

main_definition: ( transitive ) To beat, smack or slap a person's buttocks , with the bare hand or other object, as punishment, or for sexual gratification.
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To soundly defeat , to trounce .

definitions.definition: To move quickly and nimbly on foot ; to stride or run at a brisk pace.
To move or turn rapidly , as the gears of a machine or the sails of a ship.
examples: The ship was really spanking along.

definitions.definition: To shoot out or throw violently; to hurl or knock out .

main_definition: ( intransitive ) To move quickly and nimbly on foot ; to stride or run at a brisk pace.
secondary_definitions: ( intransitive ) To move or turn rapidly , as the gears of a machine or the sails of a ship.
( ambitransitive ) To shoot out or throw violently; to hurl or knock out .
